pull_request.title: CXXCBC-251: fix snappy decompression for get_replica
pull_request.body:
The library incorrectly calculates offset of the body when alternative response layout is being used (when flexible extra frames presented).

For regular get operations it is not visible, but get_replica responses contain key, and wrong offset cause snappy uncompress function to give up, and the application receives compressed payload. Which cannot be parsed as JSON.

comment.body: Out of curiosity, wasn't it the plan that the public API in couchbase-cxx-client would use std::future or std::async?

pull_request.title: Fix `premature close`, disable use of gzip/deflate.
pull_request.body:
There are bugs somewhere deep inside how simple-get, unzip-response
pump and eos all interact.  After hours of trying to diagnose, I
suggest the best option is to disable gzip/deflate for now until the root
cause is identified.

commits.message:
Increase resolution of threshold tracer up to microseconds (#219)

reporter is using microseconds to report outliers, but we store duration
with millisecond resolution, which basicaly zeroes last three digits
generate documentation using doxygen (#220)

disable doxygen on CI (#222)

there will be special step to generate API reference, which will ensure
consistent doxygen environment (version, dependencies etc.)
CXXCBC-199: Always set kv_collection_outdated retry reason on unknown collection error (#223)
fix compiler warnings about type conversions in leb128 code (#224)

CXXCBC-201 Create Doxygen output directory (#226)

Motivation
==========
On mac, doxygen fails because the doxygen output dir is not present in
the build directory.

Modification
============
Lets just create it.

Results
=======
Documentation is generated successfully.

CXXCBC-93: Use an enum for analytics metadata status (#225)

* CXXCBC-93: Use an enum for analytics metadata status

* fix formatting with 'git clang-format HEAD^'

Co-authored-by: Sergey Avseyev <sergey.avseyev@gmail.com>

SDKQE-2716: Skip analytics tests in 6.0 (#227)

The analytics service was introduced in 6.0 so there are likely bugs that are causing test failures. The failures do not occur on any later version so it is safe to disable this

CXXCBC-52: implement replica read operations (#221)

* CXXCBC-52: implement replica read operations

* refactor get replica API with bucket/scope/collection hierarchy

* update documentation for get_replica

* fix build on windows

CXXCBC-55: External Tracing and Metrics support (#228)

* CXXCBC-55: External Tracing and Metrics support

Motivation
==========
Allow clients to plug in their own tracing and/or metrics solutions,
such as OpenTelemetry

Modifications
=============
Expose the tracer and meter in cluster_options.  Then, add a parent_span
to many (but for now, not all) requests.   The tests use a simple tracer
and meter implementation to facilitate testing.

*** Will update this with a header that wraps OpenTelemetry objects in
particular, which will not be referenced by anything in the client so we
will only require otel when it is used.

Results
=======
Tests pass

* fixup tls in integration_test_guard

* Second pass at correcting tests

* fixup tracer integration test
fix division by zero issue in KV loader (#229)

split private/public API and update namespaces (#230)

* split private/public API and update namespaces

* remove namespace 'api'
CXXCBC-152: Add on error option to view request (#178)
move error codes to public API (#232)

CXXCBC-203: disable clustermap nofication by default (#233)

In order to optimize freeze/thaw cycle clustermap notification should be
disabled. Otherwise the SDK will be required to process all stale
notifications after thaw.

CXXCBC-52: fix read replica behavior for missing keys (#234)

It also exposes flags as @internal API on the result (it might be
removed later) and updates docs with code snippet of how to use the
custom transcoder

record line, file, and function names into log message (#235)

the default pattern does not include file location info to reduce
verbosity, but the tests enable it for easier debugging.
fix message for ambiguous_timeout error code (#236)

CXXCBC-55 - OpenTelemetry support (#231)

Motivation
==========
Add support to get tracing and metrics data into OpenTelemetry
providers.  Since we don't depend on otel libs or headers, these
are not referenced by any other code in the client.

Modification
============
Added headers to wrap an OpenTelemetry Tracer and Span, and one to wrap
a Meter and Histogram.  Created a stand-alone example to use each, which
will be incorporated into the source tree later when we have an examples
directory.

Results
=======
Used in my otel examples successfully.

Co-authored-by: Sergey Avseyev <sergey.avseyev@gmail.com>
CXXCBC-82: conceal not_found error for exist operation (#237)

pull_request.title: CXXCBC-52: replica reads for low-level operations
pull_request.body: Depends `operation_traits.hxx` that was introduced in #252. Has to be rebased and updated once that PR will be merged.

pull_request.title: CXXCBC-53: implement legacy durability for low-level API

review.body: Looks good to me.  I'm slightly curious why you opted to use a trait to implement the check for being a compound operation rather than using something that can be checked through the operation itself as we did with the existing execute() checks (via encoded_request_type)?  If we had some constexpr on with_legacy_durability for instance, it would save needing to explicitly define the trait for the types (and their typedefs).  It risks missing one which would cause a compilation failure.  Note that I've not used traits very much, so I genuinely don't know much about their benefits :)
